#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Getting Started"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "This chapter provides a brief introduction to &PRODUCT; and its usage, and covers how to create, configure, manage, and build a full-featured blog."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "On GNU/Linux, UNIX, and similar operating systems, you can use <command>blaze-<replaceable>command</replaceable></command> and more convenient <command>blaze <replaceable>command</replaceable></command> interchangeably. For a list of available commands, type the following at a shell prompt:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze help</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a New Blog"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To create a new blog, move into the directory in which you want to keep its working copy, and type the following at a shell prompt:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-init</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "This creates a hidden directory, <filename class=\"directory\">.blaze/</filename>, in which the blog data are stored. The actual content of this directory is not important, and it is recommended that you never touch the files in it directly."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To recover its content should it ever be damaged, use the same command again. You can also revert the existing configuration, theme, and language files to their initial state by supplying the <option>--force</option> (or <option>-f</option> for short) command line option:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-init</command> <option>-f</option>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "For a complete list of available command line options, refer to <xref linkend=\"sect-Core_Utilities-init\" />."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a New Blog in the <filename class=\"directory\">~/public_html/</filename> Directory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Many web servers are able to serve content from a certain directory within user's home directory, typically <filename class=\"directory\">~/public_html/</filename>. You can start a new blog in this directory by typing the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "public_html]$ <command>blaze-init</command>\n"
"Created a BlazeBlogger repository in .blaze."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring a Blog"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "In an attempt to make complex changes to the configuration as painless as possible, &PRODUCT; is shipped with a utility to help you with this task. To display the current value of a particular configuration option, use the <command>blaze-config</command> command followed by an option name:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <replaceable>option</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To change a configuration option, supply the new value:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <replaceable>option</replaceable> <replaceable>value</replaceable>…"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "&PRODUCT; also allows you to edit all available options at once in an external text editor. To do so, run the <command>blaze-config</command> command with the <option>--edit</option> (or <option>-e</option>) command line option:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <option>-e</option>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Note that unless the <option>core.editor</option> configuration option is already set, you must also specify a text editor to use by adding the <option>--editor</option> (or <option>-E</option>) option:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <option>-e</option> <option>-E</option> <replaceable>editor</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "The rest of this section tries to cover the most common configuration tasks, and by no means serves as a full reference. For a complete list of available configuration options, refer to <xref linkend=\"sect-Core_Utilities-config\" />."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring the Blog in <application>GVim</application>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To edit the configuration in the <application>GVim</application> text editor, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "public_html]$ <command>blaze-config -e -E \"gvim -f\"</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can set this editor as the default by typing the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "public_html]$ <command>blaze-config core.editor \"gvim -f\"</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "General Blog Settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "In order for web browsers to correctly determine the character encoding of a blog, each web page must include an appropriate information in its header. To change this information, update the <option>core.encoding</option> option with a value in the form that is recognized by W3C standards:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <option>core.encoding</option> <replaceable>encoding</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keep in mind that this option must match the character encoding you use to write the content. &PRODUCT; does not change the encoding on its own, nor does it check the value you provided. The default option is <option>UTF-8</option>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To select the document type of the generated pages, use the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <option>core.doctype</option> <replaceable>type</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Allowed options are <option>html</option> for <acronym>HTML</acronym> and <option>xhtml</option> for the <acronym>XHTML</acronym> standard. For compatibility reasons, the default option is to generate HTML pages."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Finally, to change the file extension of the generated pages, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <option>core.extension</option> <replaceable>extension</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "The changes will take effect the next time you build the blog with the <command>blaze-make</command> command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Changing the Blog Encoding"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "In most cases, the use of UTF-8 is recommended. However, if you write your blog in other encoding such as ISO-8859-2 (that is, Latin-2), type:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "public_html]$ <command>blaze-config core.encoding ISO-8859-2</command>\n"
"The option has been successfully saved."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring an RSS Feed"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To enable the creation of an RSS feed with the syndication of blog updates, supply a valid URL with the location of the blog, making sure that you include the <literal>http://</literal> (or <literal>https://</literal> if you use a secure protocol) prefix:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <option>feed.baseurl</option> <replaceable>url</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "The feed will be created the next time you build the blog with the <command>blaze-make</command> command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling the Creation of an RSS Feed"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To enable an RSS feed for a blog located at <ulink url=\"http://blaze.blackened.cz/\">http://blaze.blackened.cz/</ulink>, type the following at a shell prompt:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "public_html]$ <command>blaze-config feed.baseurl http://blaze.blackened.cz/</command>\n"
"The option has been successfully saved."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Changing a Blog Title"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To change the title of a blog, use the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <option>blog.title</option> <replaceable>title</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Beside this option, &PRODUCT; also allows you to specify the subtitle. This is typically a brief description of the blog, or a motto. To change the blog subtitle, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <option>blog.subtitle</option> <replaceable>subtitle</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "The changes will take effect the next time you run the <command>blaze-make</command> command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Changing the Blog Title and Subtitle"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To change the blog title to <quote>BlazeBlogger</quote> and the corresponding subtitle to <quote>a CMS without boundaries</quote>, type the following commands at a shell prompt:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "public_html]$ <command>blaze-config blog.title BlazeBlogger</command>\n"
"The option has been successfully saved.\n"
"public_html]$ <command>blaze-config blog.subtitle a CMS without boundaries</command>\n"
"The option has been successfully saved."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Changing a Blog Metadata"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To change the descrption of a blog, run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <option>blog.description</option> <replaceable>description</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To specify a comma-separated list of keywords that characterize the blog, type:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <option>blog.keywords</option> <replaceable>keywords</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Changing the Blog Description and Keywords"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To change the blog description to <quote>a CMS without boundaries</quote> and keywords to <quote>blazeblogger</quote>, <quote>cms</quote>, and <quote>blog</quote>, type the following at a shell prompt:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "public_html]$ <command>blaze-config blog.description a CMS without boundaries</command>\n"
"The option has been successfully saved.\n"
"public_html]$ <command>blaze-config blog.keywords blazeblogger, cms, blog</command>\n"
"The option has been successfully saved."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Changing a Blog Author"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To change the name of the author of a blog, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <option>user.name</option> <replaceable>full_name</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "This name appears in the copyright notice, and is used as the default author for a new blog post or page. However, if you prefer to keep the full name in the copyright notice only, you can specify a nickname by using the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <option>user.nickname</option> <replaceable>nickname</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Additionally, you can supply an email address to allow readers to contact the blog author directly:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <option>user.email</option> <replaceable>email_address</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Changing the Author Information"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To change the author's name to <quote>Jaromír Hradílek</quote>, author's nickname to <quote>Blackened</quote>, and the email address to <quote>jhradilek@gmail.com</quote>, type:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "public_html]$ <command>blaze-config user.name Jaromír Hradílek</command>\n"
"The option has been successfully saved.\n"
"public_html]$ <command>blaze-config user.nickname Blackened</command>\n"
"The option has been successfully saved.\n"
"public_html]$ <command>blaze-config user.email jhradilek@gmail.com</command>\n"
"The option has been successfully saved."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Changing a Blog Language"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To use a non-English translation of a blog, copy an appropriate language file to the <filename class=\"directory\">.blaze/lang/</filename> directory, and configure the blog to use this translation:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <option>blog.lang</option> <replaceable>language_code</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using the Basque Translation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "When installing &PRODUCT; on Linux, UNIX, and similar operating systems from the source code, by default, all available language files are copied to the <filename class=\"directory\">/usr/local/share/blazeblogger/lang/</filename> directory. On such system, you can change the translation of your blog to the Basque language by running the following commands:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "public_html]$ <command>cp /usr/local/share/blazeblogger/lang/eu_ES .blaze/lang/</command>\n"
"public_html]$ <command>blaze-config blog.lang eu_ES</command>\n"
"The option has been successfully saved."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Changing a Blog Theme"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To change the theme of a blog, copy the relevant files to the blog directory, and move the template and style sheet to <filename class=\"directory\">.blaze/theme/</filename> and <filename class=\"directory\">.blaze/style/</filename> respectively. Then change the configuration to use this theme by typing the following at a shell prompt:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <option>blog.theme</option> <replaceable>template_file</replaceable>\n"
"<command>blaze-config</command> <option>blog.style</option> <replaceable>stylesheet_file</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

