#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Listing Blog Posts or Pages"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To make the management of blog posts and pages easier, &PRODUCT; is shipped with the <command>blaze-list</command> utility that allows you to display the content of a blog. This includes the important information such as the identification number, date of publishing, title, and attached tags."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Since version 0.9.0, &PRODUCT; allows you to enable a colored output for some of its utilities. To enable this feature for <command>blaze-list</command>, use the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-config</command> <option>color.list</option> <option>true</option>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To display all featured blog posts, type the following at a shell prompt:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-list</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Similarly, to display a complete list of available pages, add the <option>--pages</option> (or <option>-p</option>) command line option:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-list</command> <option>-p</option>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "By default, the latest entries are listed first, and in most cases, this is a reasonable behavior. However, to change the sorting order and display the latest entries last, use the <option>--reverse</option> (or <option>-r</option>) option:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-list</command> <option>-r</option>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can also limit the number of listed entries by specifying the <option>--number</option> (or <option>-n</option>) option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-list</command> <option>-n</option> <replaceable>number</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Additionally, you can limit the output by specifying a blog post author (<option>--author</option> or <option>-a</option>), a tag (<option>--tag</option> or <option>-T</option>), a matching title (<option>--title</option> or <option>-T</option>), a date of publishing, and other criteria."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "For a complete list of available command line options, refer to <xref linkend=\"sect-Core_Utilities-list\" />."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Identifying the Very First Blog Post"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To display only the information about the first blog post, type the following at a shell prompt:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "public_html]$ <command>blaze-list -n 1 -r</command>\n"
"ID: 1 | 2009-02-10 | Jaromír Hradílek\n"
"\n"
"    Title: BlazeBlogger 0.7.0\n"
"    Tags:  release\n"
"\n"
""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generating a Blog"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To generate a complete directory tree of static pages with all blog posts, single pages, monthly and yearly archives, tags, and an RSS feed, run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-make</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Unless told otherwise, &PRODUCT; generates the blog in the current working directory. To use a different location, specify the <option>--destdir</option> (or <option>-d</option>) command line option:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-make</command> <option>-d</option> <replaceable>directory</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To display the list of files as they are created, use <option>--verbose</option> (or <option>-V</option>) command line option:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>blaze-make</command> <option>-V</option>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "For a complete list of available command line options, refer to <xref linkend=\"sect-Core_Utilities-make\" />."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you intend your blog to be accessed offline, for example, if you want to review it before you publish it on your website, use the <option>--full-paths</option> (or <option>-F</option>) option:"
